%I A396459 #15 Jun 08 2026 16:19:38
%S A396459 108,255,891,1074,1760,1792,4605,4935,6420,6812,6888,7128,8928,8932,
%T A396459 9405,11520,17336,24297,26092,31190,43392,52434,54432,60477,81594,
%U A396459 84105
%N A396459 Integers x such that there exist three integers 0<x<=y and 0<z<=t such that sigma(x)^2*psi(x) = sigma(y)^2*psi(y) = x^3 + y^3 + z^3 + t^3.
%C A396459 The numbers x, y, z and t form a sigma^2*psi-cubic quadruple.
%H A396459 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://hal.science/hal-05303937">On σψ-quadratic k-tuples and related generalizations</a>, hal-05303937, 2025.
%H A396459 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-2-psi-cubic-quadruple/blob/main/A396459">Python program</a> (github)
%e A396459 (255, 321, 84, 312) is such a quadruple because sigma(255)^2 * psi(255) = sigma(321)^2 * psi(321) = 432^2 * 432 = 255^3 + 321^3 + 84^3 + 312^3.
%o A396459 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A396459 Cf. A000203, A001615, A003327, A385397, A391534, A396076, A396309.
%K A396459 nonn,more,new
